<concept id="Java_61"
                    xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Java and Ant</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p><ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr" audience="BSS"/><ph
                    audience="app">APP</ph><ph audience="ror">The ROR integration software</ph><ph audience="aws"
                    >The AWS integration software</ph><ph audience="os">The OpenStack integration software</ph><ph
                    audience="tps5">The TPS5 integration software</ph><ph audience="vmware"
                    >The vSphere integration software</ph>
                <ph id="requires_a_Java_Development_K_concept_conbody_section_p_1"
                    >requires a Java Development Kit (JDK), version 8, 64 bit. Deployment with JDK 8, Update 121 has been tested and is recommended. </ph></p>
            <!--p
                id="Due_to_a_CORBA_library_change_concept_conbody_section_p_3">Due to a CORBA library change which is incompatible with Oracle GlassFish Server version 3.1.2.2, deployment with JDK 7, Update 55 and higher is not supported. </p-->
            <p id="For_being_able_to_execute_the_concept_conbody_section_p_2"
                    >In order to be able to execute the installation scripts, you need to install the Apache Ant 1.10 (or higher) open source software. In the subsequent sections, <codeph>&lt;ANT_HOME&gt;</codeph> is the installation directory of Apache Ant. </p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
